description.p:
That is, the present invention provides:

[1] a process for producing a methionine including the following steps (1) to (3), wherein a content of thiols in 3-methylthiopropanal is 500 ppm or less, based on the propanal, and a content of hydrogen sulfide in 3-methylthiopropanal is 60 ppm or less, based on the propanal;

step (1) in which 3-methylthiopropanal is reacted with hydrogen cyanide in the presence of a base to give 2-hydroxy-4-methylthiobutanenitrile;
step (2) in which the 2-hydroxy-4-methylthiobutanenitrile obtained in step (1) is reacted with ammonium carbonate to give 5-(β-methylmercaptoethyl) hydantoin; and
step (3) in which the 5-(p-methylmercaptoethyl)hydantoin obtained in step (2) is hydrolyzed in the presence of a basic potassium compound to give methionine;
[2] the process according to [1], wherein the thiols are 3-mercaptopropanal and/or methyl mercaptan; and the like.

Examples of the method for decreasing, as described above, the contents of the thiols and hydrogen sulfide in 3-methylthiopropanal to contents equal to or less than given contents may include:
(i) a method in which a content of hydrogen sulfide remaining is decreased by purifying the methyl mercaptan via distillation and the like, and then the resulting product is reacted with acrolein;
(ii) a method in which 3-methylthiopropanal is purified by distillation and the like, etc.

The raw material liquid for hydrolysis, as described above, was added to a zirconium autoclave in which a test piece was hanged, which was heated at 120°C for 16 hours, and a corrosion condition of the test piece was visibly confirmed (evaluation: "○" and "×"). Whether or not there is a corrosive ability of a corrosion-facilitating substance was evaluated using a reduced test piece (material: DP-3) (estimation: "corrosion" or "no corrosion").
A corrosion speed of a test piece, X (mm/y) was calculated using the following equation: X=G×365×24×10/d×S×H
wherein
X stands for a corrosion speed of a test piece [mm/y];
G stands for a value [(a weight (g) of a test piece before testing) - (a weight (g) of a test piece after testing)];
D stands for a density of a test piece [g/cm3];
S stands for an area of a test piece [cm2]; and
H stands for a testing time [h]. Corrosion speeds of a test piece of 0.02 (mm/y) or less is considered as corrosion well inhibited.

claim.claim-text:
Ein Verfahren zur Herstellung eines Methionins, umfassend die folgenden Schritte (1) bis (3), wobei ein Gehalt an Thiolen in 3-Methylthiopropanal, bezogen auf das Propanal, 500 ppm oder weniger beträgt und ein Gehalt an Schwefelwasserstoff in 3-Methylthiopropanal, bezogen auf das Propanal, 60 ppm oder weniger beträgt;

Schritt (1), bei dem 3-Methylthiopropanal mit Blausäure in Gegenwart einer Base umgesetzt wird, um 2-Hydroxy-4-methylthiobutannitril zu ergeben;

Schritt (2), bei dem das in Schritt (1) erhaltene 2-Hydroxy-4-methylthiobutannitril mit Ammoniumcarbonat umgesetzt wird, um 5-(β-Methylmercaptoethyl)hydantoin zu ergeben; und

Schritt (3), bei dem das in Schritt (2) erhaltene 5-(β-Methylmercaptoethyl)hydantoin in Gegenwart einer basischen Kaliumverbindung hydrolysiert wird, um Methionin zu ergeben.

A process for producing a methionine comprising the following steps (1) to (3), wherein a content of thiols in 3-methylthiopropanal is 500 ppm or less, based on the propanal, and a content of hydrogen sulfide in 3-methylthiopropanal is 60 ppm or less, based on the propanal;

step (1) in which 3-methylthiopropanal is reacted with hydrogen cyanide in the presence of a base to give 2-hydroxy-4-methylthiobutanenitrile;

step (2) in which the 2-hydroxy-4-methylthiobutanenitrile obtained in step (1) is reacted with ammonium carbonate to give 5-(β-methylmercaptoethyl)hydantoin; and

step (3) in which the 5-(β-methylmercaptoethyl)hydantoin obtained in step (2) is hydrolyzed in the presence of a basic potassium compound to give methionine.

Procédé de production de méthionine comprenant les étapes (1) à (3) suivantes, dans lequel une teneur des thiols dans le 3-méthylthiopropanal est de 500 ppm ou moins, par rapport au propanal, et une teneur du sulfure d'hydrogène dans le 3-méthylthiopropanal est de 60 ppm ou moins, par rapport au propanal ;

étape (1) dans laquelle le 3-méthylthiopropanal est mis à réagir avec du cyanure d'hydrogène en présence d'une base pour donner du 2-hydroxy-4-méthylthiobutanenitrile ;

étape (2) dans laquelle le 2-hydroxy-4-méthylthiobutanenitrile obtenu dans l'étape (1) est mis à réagir avec du carbonate d'ammonium pour donner de la 5-(β-méthylmercaptoéthyl)hydantoïne ; et

étape (3) dans laquelle la 5-(β-méthylmercaptoéthyl)hydantoïne obtenue dans l'étape (2) est hydrolysée en présence d'un composé basique à base de potassium pour donner de la méthionine.
